@startuml
' -------------------------------------------------
' Load the official ArchiMate library for PlantUML
' -------------------------------------------------
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/archimate/master/archimate.puml

' -------------------------------------------------
' 1️⃣  DATA OBJECTS (the actual data sets)
' -------------------------------------------------
archimate "Raw Data Set"          as RawData   <<Data Object>>
archimate "Cleaned Data Set"      as CleanData <<Data Object>>
archimate "Aggregated Data Set"   as AggData   <<Data Object>>

' -------------------------------------------------
' 2️⃣  APPLICATION COMPONENTS (the processes that
'     transform the data)
' -------------------------------------------------
archimate "Data‑Cleaning Service"   as Cleaning   <<Application Component>>
archimate "Aggregation Service"     as Aggregator <<Application Component>>

' -------------------------------------------------
' 3️⃣  DATA‑LINEAGE RELATIONSHIPS
' -------------------------------------------------
' a) The cleaning service reads the raw data
RawData   -[#black]-> Cleaning   : Access

' b) The cleaning service creates the cleaned data set
Cleaning  -[#black]-> CleanData : Realization

' c) The aggregation service reads the cleaned data
CleanData -[#black]-> Aggregator : Access

' d) The aggregation service creates the aggregated data set
Aggregator -[#black]-> AggData   : Realization

' -------------------------------------------------
' 4️⃣  Layout hints (optional, just to keep the diagram tidy)
' -------------------------------------------------
' Stack the three data objects vertically
RawData   -[hidden]-> CleanData
CleanData -[hidden]-> AggData

' Place the services to the right of the data they consume
Cleaning   -[hidden]-> RawData
Aggregator -[hidden]-> CleanData
@enduml